      <body>
         <entry xml:id="mantilin-ys"
            type="mainEntry"
            xml:lang="en"
            prev="#manwalin-dlgenr"
            next="#mastikhe-dlgenr"
            source="Yalkut Shimoni">
            <form type="lemma">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">מנטילין</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">mnṭylyn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic">manṭilin</pron>
               <gramGrp>
                  <gram type="pos">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen">m.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="mantilin-ys-1">
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>towel, napkin</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <quote>μαντίλιον</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>למלך שבנה פלטין והושיב בהן דיורין אלמים והיו משכימים ושואלים בשלום המלך ברמיזה ובאצבע ובמטולין</quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq 7</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">I 25: 27</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">פלטין</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>It is as if a king built a palace and tenanted it with dumb people, who used to rise early and pay their respects to the king with gestures, with their fingers and with their handkerchiefs.</quote>
                  </cit>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>למלך שבנה פלטין והושיב בהן דיורים אלמים והיו משכימים ושואלים בשלום המלך באצבע ברמיזה 
                     <app>
                        <lem>ובמטולין</lem>
                        <rdg wit="#W">ובמנולין</rdg>
                     </app>
                  </quote>
                  <bibl>
                     <ref type="witness">Yalq Ps 848</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">473d: 3</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">פלטין</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>It is as if a king built a palace and tenanted it with dumb people, who used to rise early and pay their respects to the king with their fingers, gestures and with their handkerchiefs.</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note>= <bibl type="ancient">GenR 5,1 [I 32: 4.5]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">ובמנולים</term> and <term xml:lang="jpa">ובמנוולים</term>); <bibl type="ancient">GenR 28,2 [I 260: 6]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">ובמנוולים</term>); <bibl type="ancient">LamR 1,16 [40a]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">בסודרין</term>); <bibl type="ancient">YalqM 93,12 [II 52b]</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">ובמטולין</term> corrected <term xml:lang="jpa">ובנמולים</term>)</note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <note>For the lemma in <bibl type="ancient">GenR</bibl> cf. <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa" target="manwalin.html">מנוולין</ref>. Krauss considers the reading in <bibl type="ancient">GenR</bibl> as corruption of <term xml:lang="jpa">מנטילין</term>.</note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl>
                  <title>Krauss, LW II</title>
                  <citedRange>343ab</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
